                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230409-206-off1101 t18230409-206-crimeloc1104"></join>. On the 13th of March, this bright stake lay in the shop. The prisoner was walking up and down before the door, but I did not suspect him; in about ten minutes I was sent for to do a job opposite, and left my wife in the shop. On coming out of the door, I saw him running from my door with something under his waistcoat - I went after him, and asked what he had got; he said nothing. I took it from him. He pleaded distress.</p>
